{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"This is the Large Hadron Collider."},{"time":4000,"text":"It's 27 kilometers in circumference."},{"time":6000,"text":"It's the biggest scientific experiment ever attempted."},{"time":9000,"text":"Over 10,000 physicists and engineers"},{"time":12000,"text":"from 85 countries around the world"},{"time":14000,"text":"have come together over several decades"},{"time":16000,"text":"to build this machine."},{"time":18000,"text":"What we do is we accelerate protons --"},{"time":20000,"text":"so, hydrogen nuclei --"},{"time":22000,"text":"around 99.999999"},{"time":26000,"text":"percent the speed of light."},{"time":28000,"text":"Right? At that speed, they go around"},{"time":30000,"text":"that 27 kilometers 11,000 times a second."},{"time":34000,"text":"And we collide them with another beam of protons"},{"time":36000,"text":"going in the opposite direction."},{"time":39000,"text":"We collide them inside giant detectors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":41000,"text":"They're essentially digital cameras."},{"time":43000,"text":"And this is the one that I work on, ATLAS."},{"time":45000,"text":"You get some sense of the size --"},{"time":47000,"text":"you can just see these EU standard-size"},{"time":49000,"text":"people underneath."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":53000,"text":"You get some sense of the size: 44 meters wide,"},{"time":56000,"text":"22 meters in diameter, 7,000 tons."},{"time":59000,"text":"And we re-create the conditions that were present"},{"time":62000,"text":"less than a billionth of a second after the universe began"},{"time":65000,"text":"up to 600 million times a second"},{"time":67000,"text":"inside that detector -- immense numbers."},{"time":71000,"text":"And if you see those metal bits there --"},{"time":73000,"text":"those are huge magnets that bend"},{"time":75000,"text":"electrically charged particles,"},{"time":77000,"text":"so it can measure how fast they're traveling."},{"time":79000,"text":"This is a picture about a year ago."},{"time":81000,"text":"Those magnets are in there."},{"time":83000,"text":"And, again, a EU standard-size, real person,"},{"time":85000,"text":"so you get some sense of the scale."},{"time":88000,"text":"And it's in there that those mini-Big Bangs will be created,"},{"time":90000,"text":"sometime in the summer this year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92000,"text":"And actually, this morning, I got an email"},{"time":94000,"text":"saying that we've just finished, today,"},{"time":96000,"text":"building the last piece of ATLAS."},{"time":98000,"text":"So as of today, it's finished. I'd like to say"},{"time":100000,"text":"that I planned that for TED,"},{"time":102000,"text":"but I didn't. So it's been completed as of today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":109000,"text":"Yeah, it's a wonderful achievement."},{"time":111000,"text":"So, you might be asking, \"Why?"},{"time":113000,"text":"Why create the conditions that were present"},{"time":115000,"text":"less than a billionth of a second after the universe began?\""},{"time":118000,"text":"Well, particle physicists are nothing if not ambitious."},{"time":121000,"text":"And the aim of particle physics is to understand"},{"time":124000,"text":"what everything's made of, and how everything sticks together."},{"time":127000,"text":"And by everything I mean, of course,"},{"time":129000,"text":"me and you, the Earth, the Sun,"},{"time":132000,"text":"the 100 billion suns in our galaxy"},{"time":135000,"text":"and the 100 billion galaxies"},{"time":137000,"text":"in the observable universe."},{"time":139000,"text":"Absolutely everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141000,"text":"Now you might say, \"Well, OK, but why not just look at it?"},{"time":143000,"text":"You know? If you want to know what I'm made of, let's look at me.\""},{"time":146000,"text":"Well, we found that as you look back in time,"},{"time":149000,"text":"the universe gets hotter and hotter,"},{"time":152000,"text":"denser and denser, and simpler and simpler."},{"time":155000,"text":"Now, there's no real reason I'm aware of for that,"},{"time":157000,"text":"but that seems to be the case."},{"time":160000,"text":"So, way back in the early times of the universe,"},{"time":162000,"text":"we believe it was very simple and understandable."},{"time":165000,"text":"All this complexity, all the way to these wonderful things --"},{"time":168000,"text":"human brains -- are a property of an old"},{"time":170000,"text":"and cold and complicated universe."},{"time":173000,"text":"Back at the start, in the first billionth of a second,"},{"time":176000,"text":"we believe, or we've observed, it was very simple."}]},{"cues":[{"time":178000,"text":"It's almost like ..."},{"time":180000,"text":"imagine a snowflake in your hand,"},{"time":182000,"text":"and you look at it, and it's an incredibly complicated,"},{"time":185000,"text":"beautiful object. But as you heat it up,"},{"time":188000,"text":"it'll melt into a pool of water,"},{"time":191000,"text":"and you would be able to see that, actually, it was just made"},{"time":193000,"text":"of H20, water."},{"time":196000,"text":"So it's in that same sense that we look back in time"},{"time":198000,"text":"to understand what the universe is made of."},{"time":201000,"text":"And, as of today, it's made of these things."},{"time":204000,"text":"Just 12 particles of matter,"},{"time":206000,"text":"stuck together by four forces of nature."},{"time":210000,"text":"The quarks, these pink things, are the things that make up protons and neutrons"},{"time":213000,"text":"that make up the atomic nuclei in your body."},{"time":216000,"text":"The electron -- the thing that goes around"},{"time":218000,"text":"the atomic nucleus --"},{"time":220000,"text":"held around in orbit, by the way, by the electromagnetic force"},{"time":223000,"text":"that's carried by this thing, the photon."},{"time":225000,"text":"The quarks are stuck together by other things called gluons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":228000,"text":"And these guys, here, they're the weak nuclear force,"},{"time":230000,"text":"probably the least familiar."},{"time":232000,"text":"But, without it, the sun wouldn't shine."},{"time":234000,"text":"And when the sun shines, you get copious quantities"},{"time":236000,"text":"of these things, called neutrinos, pouring out."},{"time":239000,"text":"Actually, if you just look at your thumbnail --"},{"time":242000,"text":"about a square centimeter --"},{"time":245000,"text":"there are something like 60 billion neutrinos per second"},{"time":248000,"text":"from the sun, passing"},{"time":250000,"text":"through every square centimeter of your body."},{"time":252000,"text":"But you don't feel them, because the weak force"},{"time":254000,"text":"is correctly named --"},{"time":256000,"text":"very short range and very weak,"},{"time":258000,"text":"so they just fly through you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"And these particles have been discovered"},{"time":262000,"text":"over the last century, pretty much."},{"time":264000,"text":"The first one, the electron, was discovered in 1897,"},{"time":266000,"text":"and the last one, this thing called the tau neutrino,"},{"time":269000,"text":"in the year 2000. Actually just --"},{"time":271000,"text":"I was going to say, just up the road in Chicago. I know it's a big country,"},{"time":274000,"text":"America, isn't it?"},{"time":277000,"text":"Just up the road."},{"time":280000,"text":"Relative to the universe, it's just up the road."}]},{"cues":[{"time":283000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":285000,"text":"So, this thing was discovered in the year 2000,"},{"time":287000,"text":"so it's a relatively recent picture."},{"time":290000,"text":"One of the wonderful things, actually, I find,"},{"time":292000,"text":"is that we've discovered any of them, when you realize how tiny they are."},{"time":295000,"text":"You know, they're a step in size"},{"time":297000,"text":"from the entire observable universe."},{"time":299000,"text":"So, 100 billion galaxies,"},{"time":301000,"text":"13.7 billion light years away --"},{"time":304000,"text":"a step in size from that to Monterey, actually,"},{"time":307000,"text":"is about the same as from Monterey to these things."},{"time":310000,"text":"Absolutely, exquisitely minute,"},{"time":313000,"text":"and yet we've discovered pretty much the full set."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317000,"text":"So, one of my most illustrious forebears"},{"time":320000,"text":"at Manchester University, Ernest Rutherford,"},{"time":322000,"text":"discoverer of the atomic nucleus,"},{"time":324000,"text":"once said, \"All science is either physics"},{"time":326000,"text":"or stamp collecting.\""},{"time":328000,"text":"Now, I don't think he meant to insult"},{"time":331000,"text":"the rest of science,"},{"time":333000,"text":"although he was from New Zealand, so it's possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":336000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338000,"text":"But what he meant was that what we've done, really,"},{"time":340000,"text":"is stamp collect there."},{"time":342000,"text":"OK, we've discovered the particles,"},{"time":344000,"text":"but unless you understand the underlying"},{"time":346000,"text":"reason for that pattern -- you know, why it's built the way it is --"},{"time":349000,"text":"really you've done stamp collecting. You haven't done science."},{"time":352000,"text":"Fortunately, we have"},{"time":354000,"text":"probably one of the greatest scientific achievements of the twentieth century"},{"time":357000,"text":"that underpins that pattern."},{"time":359000,"text":"It's the Newton's laws, if you want,"},{"time":361000,"text":"of particle physics."},{"time":363000,"text":"It's called the standard model -- beautifully simple mathematical equation."},{"time":366000,"text":"You could stick it on the front of a T-shirt,"},{"time":368000,"text":"which is always the sign of elegance."},{"time":371000,"text":"This is it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":375000,"text":"I've been a little disingenuous, because I've expanded it out"},{"time":377000,"text":"in all its gory detail."},{"time":379000,"text":"This equation, though, allows you to calculate everything --"},{"time":381000,"text":"other than gravity -- that happens in the universe."},{"time":384000,"text":"So, you want to know why the sky is blue, why atomic nuclei stick together --"},{"time":387000,"text":"in principle, you've got a big enough computer --"},{"time":389000,"text":"why DNA is the shape it is."},{"time":391000,"text":"In principle, you should be able to calculate it from that equation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":394000,"text":"But there's a problem."},{"time":397000,"text":"Can anyone see what it is?"},{"time":401000,"text":"A bottle of champagne for anyone that tells me."},{"time":404000,"text":"I'll make it easier, actually, by blowing one of the lines up."},{"time":407000,"text":"Basically, each of these terms"},{"time":409000,"text":"refers to some of the particles."},{"time":411000,"text":"So those Ws there refer to the Ws, and how they stick together."},{"time":414000,"text":"These carriers of the weak force, the Zs, the same."},{"time":417000,"text":"But there's an extra symbol in this equation: H."},{"time":419000,"text":"Right, H."},{"time":421000,"text":"H stands for Higgs particle."},{"time":423000,"text":"Higgs particles have not been discovered."},{"time":426000,"text":"But they're necessary: they're necessary"},{"time":428000,"text":"to make that mathematics work."},{"time":430000,"text":"So all the exquisitely detailed calculations we can do"},{"time":432000,"text":"with that wonderful equation"},{"time":434000,"text":"wouldn't be possible without an extra bit."},{"time":436000,"text":"So it's a prediction:"},{"time":438000,"text":"a prediction of a new particle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":440000,"text":"What does it do?"},{"time":442000,"text":"Well, we had a long time to come up with good analogies."},{"time":444000,"text":"And back in the 1980s, when we wanted the money"},{"time":447000,"text":"for the LHC from the U.K. government,"},{"time":449000,"text":"Margaret Thatcher, at the time, said,"},{"time":451000,"text":"\"If you guys can explain, in language"},{"time":453000,"text":"a politician can understand,"},{"time":455000,"text":"what the hell it is that you're doing, you can have the money."},{"time":458000,"text":"I want to know what this Higgs particle does.\""},{"time":460000,"text":"And we came up with this analogy, and it seemed to work."},{"time":462000,"text":"Well, what the Higgs does is, it gives mass to the fundamental particles."},{"time":465000,"text":"And the picture is that the whole universe --"},{"time":467000,"text":"and that doesn't mean just space, it means me as well, and inside you --"},{"time":470000,"text":"the whole universe is full of something called a Higgs field."},{"time":473000,"text":"Higgs particles, if you will."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475000,"text":"The analogy is that these people in a room"},{"time":477000,"text":"are the Higgs particles."},{"time":479000,"text":"Now when a particle moves through the universe,"},{"time":481000,"text":"it can interact with these Higgs particles."},{"time":484000,"text":"But imagine someone who's not very popular moves through the room."},{"time":487000,"text":"Then everyone ignores them. They can just pass through the room very quickly,"},{"time":490000,"text":"essentially at the speed of light. They're massless."},{"time":493000,"text":"And imagine someone incredibly important"},{"time":495000,"text":"and popular and intelligent"},{"time":497000,"text":"walks into the room."},{"time":500000,"text":"They're surrounded by people, and their passage through the room is impeded."},{"time":503000,"text":"It's almost like they get heavy. They get massive."},{"time":506000,"text":"And that's exactly the way the Higgs mechanism works."},{"time":509000,"text":"The picture is that the electrons and the quarks"},{"time":511000,"text":"in your body and in the universe that we see around us"},{"time":514000,"text":"are heavy, in a sense, and massive,"},{"time":516000,"text":"because they're surrounded by Higgs particles."},{"time":518000,"text":"They're interacting with the Higgs field."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521000,"text":"If that picture's true,"},{"time":523000,"text":"then we have to discover those Higgs particles at the LHC."},{"time":527000,"text":"If it's not true -- because it's quite a convoluted mechanism,"},{"time":529000,"text":"although it's the simplest we've been able to think of --"},{"time":532000,"text":"then whatever does the job of the Higgs particles"},{"time":534000,"text":"we know have to turn up"},{"time":536000,"text":"at the LHC."},{"time":538000,"text":"So, that's one of the prime reasons we built this giant machine."},{"time":541000,"text":"I'm glad you recognize Margaret Thatcher."},{"time":543000,"text":"Actually, I thought about making it more culturally relevant, but --"},{"time":546000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":549000,"text":"anyway."},{"time":551000,"text":"So that's one thing."},{"time":553000,"text":"That's essentially a guarantee of what the LHC will find."}]},{"cues":[{"time":556000,"text":"There are many other things. You've heard"},{"time":558000,"text":"many of the big problems in particle physics."},{"time":560000,"text":"One of them you heard about: dark matter, dark energy."},{"time":563000,"text":"There's another issue,"},{"time":565000,"text":"which is that the forces in nature -- it's quite beautiful, actually --"},{"time":567000,"text":"seem, as you go back in time,"},{"time":569000,"text":"they seem to change in strength."},{"time":571000,"text":"Well, they do change in strength."},{"time":573000,"text":"So, the electromagnetic force, the force that holds us together,"},{"time":576000,"text":"gets stronger as you go to higher temperatures."},{"time":579000,"text":"The strong force, the strong nuclear force, which sticks nuclei together,"},{"time":582000,"text":"gets weaker. And what you see is the standard model --"},{"time":585000,"text":"you can calculate how these change -- is the forces,"},{"time":587000,"text":"the three forces, other than gravity,"},{"time":589000,"text":"almost seem to come together at one point."},{"time":591000,"text":"It's almost as if there was one beautiful"},{"time":593000,"text":"kind of super-force, back at the beginning of time."},{"time":596000,"text":"But they just miss."}]},{"cues":[{"time":598000,"text":"Now there's a theory called super-symmetry,"},{"time":600000,"text":"which doubles the number of particles in the standard model,"},{"time":603000,"text":"which, at first sight, doesn't sound like a simplification."},{"time":605000,"text":"But actually, with this theory,"},{"time":607000,"text":"we find that the forces of nature"},{"time":609000,"text":"do seem to unify together, back at the Big Bang --"},{"time":612000,"text":"absolutely beautiful prophecy. The model wasn't built to do that,"},{"time":615000,"text":"but it seems to do it."},{"time":617000,"text":"Also, those super-symmetric particles"},{"time":619000,"text":"are very strong candidates for the dark matter."},{"time":621000,"text":"So a very compelling theory"},{"time":623000,"text":"that's really mainstream physics."},{"time":625000,"text":"And if I was to put money on it, I would put money on --"},{"time":627000,"text":"in a very unscientific way -- that"},{"time":629000,"text":"that these things would also crop up at the LHC."},{"time":632000,"text":"Many other things that the LHC could discover."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635000,"text":"But in the last few minutes, I just want to give you"},{"time":638000,"text":"a different perspective"},{"time":640000,"text":"of what I think -- what particle physics"},{"time":642000,"text":"really means to me -- particle physics and cosmology."},{"time":645000,"text":"And that's that I think it's given us a wonderful"},{"time":648000,"text":"narrative -- almost a creation story,"},{"time":651000,"text":"if you'd like -- about the universe,"},{"time":653000,"text":"from modern science over the last few decades."},{"time":656000,"text":"And I'd say that it deserves,"},{"time":658000,"text":"in the spirit of Wade Davis' talk,"},{"time":660000,"text":"to be at least put up there with these wonderful creation stories"},{"time":663000,"text":"of the peoples of the high Andes and the frozen north."},{"time":667000,"text":"This is a creation story, I think, equally as wonderful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671000,"text":"The story goes like this: we know that"},{"time":673000,"text":"the universe began 13.7 billion years ago,"},{"time":676000,"text":"in an immensely hot, dense state,"},{"time":679000,"text":"much smaller than a single atom."},{"time":681000,"text":"It began to expand about"},{"time":683000,"text":"a million, billion, billion, billion billionth"},{"time":686000,"text":"of a second -- I think I got that right -- after the Big Bang."},{"time":690000,"text":"Gravity separated away from the other forces."},{"time":692000,"text":"The universe then underwent"},{"time":694000,"text":"an exponential expansion called inflation."},{"time":697000,"text":"In about the first billionth of a second or so,"},{"time":699000,"text":"the Higgs field kicked in, and the quarks"},{"time":701000,"text":"and the gluons and the electrons"},{"time":704000,"text":"that make us up got mass."},{"time":706000,"text":"The universe continued to expand and cool."},{"time":709000,"text":"After about a few minutes,"},{"time":711000,"text":"there was hydrogen and helium in the universe. That's all."},{"time":714000,"text":"The universe was about 75 percent hydrogen,"},{"time":717000,"text":"25 percent helium. It still is today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":720000,"text":"It continued to expand"},{"time":722000,"text":"about 300 million years."},{"time":724000,"text":"Then light began to travel through the universe."},{"time":726000,"text":"It was big enough to be transparent to light,"},{"time":728000,"text":"and that's what we see in the cosmic microwave background"},{"time":730000,"text":"that George Smoot described"},{"time":732000,"text":"as looking at the face of God."},{"time":734000,"text":"After about 400 million years, the first stars formed,"},{"time":737000,"text":"and that hydrogen, that helium, then began to cook"},{"time":739000,"text":"into the heavier elements."},{"time":741000,"text":"So the elements of life --"},{"time":743000,"text":"carbon, and oxygen and iron,"},{"time":745000,"text":"all the elements that we need to make us up --"},{"time":747000,"text":"were cooked in those first generations of stars,"},{"time":750000,"text":"which then ran out of fuel, exploded,"},{"time":752000,"text":"threw those elements back into the universe."},{"time":755000,"text":"They then re-collapsed into another generation"},{"time":757000,"text":"of stars and planets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":760000,"text":"And on some of those planets, the oxygen, which had been created"},{"time":763000,"text":"in that first generation of stars, could fuse with hydrogen"},{"time":766000,"text":"to form water, liquid water on the surface."},{"time":769000,"text":"On at least one, and maybe only one of those planets,"},{"time":772000,"text":"primitive life evolved,"},{"time":775000,"text":"which evolved over millions of years into"},{"time":777000,"text":"things that walked upright and left footprints"},{"time":779000,"text":"about three and a half million years ago in the mud flats of Tanzania,"},{"time":782000,"text":"and eventually"},{"time":784000,"text":"left a footprint on another world."},{"time":786000,"text":"And built this civilization,"},{"time":788000,"text":"this wonderful picture,"},{"time":790000,"text":"that turned the darkness into light,"},{"time":793000,"text":"and you can see the civilization from space."},{"time":795000,"text":"As one of my great heroes, Carl Sagan, said,"},{"time":798000,"text":"these are the things -- and actually, not only these,"},{"time":800000,"text":"but I was looking around -- these are the things,"},{"time":802000,"text":"like Saturn V rockets, and Sputnik,"},{"time":805000,"text":"and DNA, and literature and science --"},{"time":807000,"text":"these are the things that hydrogen atoms do"},{"time":809000,"text":"when given 13.7 billion years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":813000,"text":"Absolutely remarkable."},{"time":815000,"text":"And, the laws of physics. Right?"},{"time":817000,"text":"So, the right laws of physics --"},{"time":819000,"text":"they're beautifully balanced."},{"time":821000,"text":"If the weak force had been a little bit different,"},{"time":823000,"text":"then carbon and oxygen wouldn't be stable"},{"time":825000,"text":"inside the hearts of stars,"},{"time":827000,"text":"and there would be none of that in the universe."},{"time":830000,"text":"And I think that's"},{"time":832000,"text":"a wonderful and significant story."},{"time":834000,"text":"50 years ago, I couldn't have told that story,"},{"time":836000,"text":"because we didn't know it."},{"time":838000,"text":"It makes me really feel that"},{"time":840000,"text":"that civilization --"},{"time":842000,"text":"which, as I say, if you believe"},{"time":844000,"text":"the scientific creation story,"},{"time":846000,"text":"has emerged purely as a result of the laws of physics,"},{"time":849000,"text":"and a few hydrogen atoms --"},{"time":851000,"text":"then I think, to me anyway,"},{"time":854000,"text":"it makes me feel incredibly valuable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"So that's the LHC."},{"time":858000,"text":"The LHC is certainly, when it turns on in summer,"},{"time":861000,"text":"going to write the next chapter of that book."},{"time":864000,"text":"And I'm certainly looking forward with"},{"time":866000,"text":"immense excitement to it being turned on."},{"time":868000,"text":"Thanks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":870000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}